aLang.ESL_ENABLE_Byte_Description:
Offset[0x00]  
TAG: ESL_ENABLE  

Enemy activity status when entering room, 
0x00: Deactivated, 
0x01: Activated. 
No other values are valid.

Offset[0x01][0x02]  
TAG: ESL_ENEMY_ID  

This is the ID of the enemy placed in the Room.
aLang.ESL_EnemyLifeAmount_Short_Description:
Offset[0x09][0x08]  
TAG: ESL_LIFE  

Enemy life value, 
Max value is set to 32767, 
e Negative numbers will cause the enemy to be immortal.
aLang.ESL_ROOM_ID_Ushort_Description:
Offset[0x19][0x18]  
TAG: ESL_ROOM_ID  

Enemy's Room ID | represents the ID of the room where the enemy is being added.

Offset[<<Offset1>>][<<Offset2>>]  
TAG: ETCMODEL_ID  

ETCMODEL model ID, Warning: the ID must exist in .ETM file, otherwise, the object will not appear in game.
aLang.ETS_ID_Ushort_Description:
Offset[<<Offset1>>][<<Offset2>>]  
TAG: ETS_ID  

Object unique identifier (index). 
The valid range for the index lay betwen 0x00 and 0x3F, values above are not loaded, 
index values can be repeated any amount of times, 
but, only 99 valid objects can be loaded to the scenario.

aLang.MessageColor_Byte_Description:
Offset[0x53]  
TAG: MessageColor  

Color of the displayed message, being: 
00: Default or White 
01: Green 
02: Red 
 Another Value: Aka Default

aLang.LockedDoorType_Byte_Description:
Offset[<<Offset1>>]  
TAG: LockedDoorType  

Door status. 
00: Opened, free access. 
01: Locked.
02: Unlock door.
Other values: unknown.
aLang.LadderStepCount_Sbyte_Description:
Offset[<<Offset1>>]  
TAG: LadderStepCount  

Ladder steps number, considering that: 
For positive values the player will climb. 
For negative values the player will go down the stairs. 
Do not use the values -1, 0 and +1, as the player will stay in the ladder animation infinitely.
